modules.description: Extracts and converts values from parsed data, including converting a list of tokens into a structured value and a remaining token list. Works with strings, tables, and custom value types derived from token sequences. Parses raw strings into internal representations for further processing.

Converts a list of characters into a list of tokens and generates a string representation of a token. Operates on character lists and abstract token types. Used to process input streams into structured token sequences for parsing or analysis.
Converts between a list of characters and a string. Operates on char lists and strings. Used to prepare character sequences for output or process raw string data as lists.

Provides functions for parsing and validating OpenAPI 3.0 specification files, including loading YAML or JSON documents, extracting paths and operations, and checking required fields. Works with structured data types such as maps, lists, and custom records representing API endpoints, parameters, and responses. Used to generate client code from API definitions and perform schema consistency checks during development.

Processes character sequences into structured tokens and back, enabling parsing, conversion, and manipulation of data from raw input to internal representations. Supports operations on strings, character lists, and tokens, allowing for value extraction, token generation, and string reconstruction. Can transform token lists into structured values, convert characters to tokens, and serialize tokens back to strings. Enables tasks like parsing configuration data, analyzing input streams, and generating output from internal representations.
